---

# Task

Cite given conversation in <Conversation> exactly, but transform specific cases as defined under **Repeated Messages**, **Split Messages**, **Partial Messages** and **Unnecessary Appeals**.


## **Repeated Messages**

- Listed in a row from the same person
- Each next message duplicates previous
- The first message only must be kept

<Example alt="repeated messages" role="input">
User: Hi there
User: Hi there
User: Hi there
</Example>

<Output alt="transformed repeated messages" role="output">
User: Hi there
</Output>


## **Partial Messages**

- Listed in a row from the same person
- Each next message contains the same beginning but ends with one or more new words
- The last (complete) message only must be kept

<Example alt="partial messages" role="input">
User: Hi
User: Hi there
User: Hi there, nice
User: Hi there, nice to
User: Hi there, nice to meet you
</Example>

<Output alt="transformed partial messages" role="output">
User: Hi there, nice to meet you
</Output>


## **Split Messages**

- Listed in a row from the same person
- The full message has been split into two or more messages and are a part of a single message
- The composition of all parts must be kept

<Example alt="split messages" role="input">
User: I want to,
User: make an appointment
</Example>

<Output alt="transformed split messages" role="output">
User: I want to, make an appointment
</Output>


## **Unnecessary Appeals**

- ConvoAgent greetings, thanks or appeals to the User at the message beginning.

<Example alt="unnecessary appeal messages" role="input">
ConvoAgent: Welcome to ...
User: Hello! I want to ...
ConvoAgent: Hello! Certainly! I can help you with that. May I know your name please?
User: I am John Doe!
ConvoAgent: Hello John Doe! Please provide your ...
</Example>

<Output alt="unnecessary appeal messages" role="output">
ConvoAgent: Welcome to ...
User: Hello! I want to ...
ConvoAgent: Hello! Certainly! I can help you with that. May I know your name please?
User: I am John Doe!
ConvoAgent: Please provide your ...
</Output>


## Additionally
- If the message includes numbers, dates, or times, wrap them using markdown with double asterisks (e.g., **bold**).
- ALWAYS keep messages about the actions the ConvoAgent has just did (e.g. "I've just sent ...", "I've just noted ...")


# Output format

Keep original conversation history format:
- Each turn on a separate line
- Do not output `<Conversation>` annotation

# Output

{{~/system}}

{{Set(name="corrected_memory", value=Gen(temperature=0.2, topP=0.6, thinkingBudget=425))}}

{{Return(val=corrected_memory)}}
